  <titles>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Second Amendment Protection Act of 2011</title>
    <title type="display">Second Amendment Protection Act of 2011</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">To express the sense of the Congress that the United States should not adopt any treaty that poses a threat to national sovereignty or abridges any rights guaranteed by the United States Constitution, such as the right to keep and bear arms, and to withhold funding from the United Nations unless the President certifies that the United Nations has not taken action to restrict, attempt to restrict, or otherwise adversely infringe upon the rights of individuals in the United States to keep and bear arms, or abridge any of the other constitutionally protected rights of citizens of the United States.</title>
  </titles>
